org.hibernate.ogm.datastore.mongodb.query.parsing.nativequery.impl

Class NativeQueryParser

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.parboiled.BaseActions<V>
      • org.parboiled.BaseParser<MongoDBQueryDescriptorBuilder>
        • org.hibernate.ogm.datastore.mongodb.query.parsing.nativequery.impl.NativeQueryParser
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    org.parboiled.ContextAware<MongoDBQueryDescriptorBuilder>

    public class NativeQueryParser
extends org.parboiled.BaseParser<MongoDBQueryDescriptorBuilder>
    A parser for MongoDB queries which can be given in one of the following representations:
    • Criteria-only find query, e.g. { $and: [ { name : 'Portia' }, { author : 'Oscar Wilde' } ] }. It is left to MongoDB's own JSON parser to interpret such queries.
    • As "invocation" of the MongoDB shell API, e.g. db.WILDE_POEM.find({ '$query' : { 'name' : 'Athanasia' }, '$orderby' : { 'name' : 1 } }). Currently the following API methods are supported:
      • find(criteria)
      • find(criteria, projection)
      The parameter values must be given as JSON objects adhering to the strict mode of MongoDB's JSON handling, with the relaxation that Strings may not only be given in double quotes but also single quotes to facilitate their specification in Java Strings.
    Author:
    Gunnar Morling
